Class FE_table_model

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.table.TableModel
public class FE_table_model
extends javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel

Overview
The FE_table_model class is based on the abstract table model and is used to store the data appearing in the jtables in the UCD 2001 front end.

Version:
1.0 (December 2001)
Author:
Tony Held

Data

private java.util.Vector Data
Table Data is stored in the data member. The table data is stored in a vector to allow the addition and deletion of rows. Each member of the data vector contains a 1-D object array with data for a single row.
Constructor Detail

FE_table_model

public FE_table_model(java.lang.String[] ColumnNames,
                      java.lang.Object[][] Data)
Constructor that assigns column names and data to the table model. The parameter arrays are cloned so that the data holds its own copy of the data. The Data parameter must be a rectangular matrix. The number of columns in columnNames and Data must agree. The table_model will store its own copy of the data passed to the object based on the parameter data.
